<br>
At your mid to upper 40's, concentrate on easily attainable items that have either High int or High cha. Focus on keeping both int and cha about evenly high up there. You can have some major cha gear for when you know you will be charming a lot, but simply concentrate on keepng both stats as high as you can.<br>
<br>
When you acquire enough cash you will want to start looking for items that fulfill multiple roles. A great example of this is the Int bracer in Umbral. 15 int, High AC, and resists. The cha bracer from there is nice also. As one of the other posters stated, the High end of the game will change what you want to wear. You can safely keep your base int and cha lower than 255 because your buffs will bring it up to if nor past 255. This is when you will start wanting to acquire the hp/mana items. Stamina items also add to your hp, and ac will help lower your damage taken slightly.<br>
<br>
So....  Don't spend a whole lot of money on a +15 cha, ac 4 hat. Because in 5 or so levels you'll have a new cha buff that will make it useless. Another good way to find out what you should be buying is to look at a bnch of lvl 60 chanters Magelo profiles. See what items they have that are in your price range. Odds are if they're wearing it, it provides stats that are important. <p><font size="2" face="Verdana,Arial">
<br>
<b>Slymie aka Garin</b><br>
Living By Chance, Loving By Choice, Charming By Profession <br>
